    <title type="text">Speculum Romanae Magnificentiae</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://speculum.lib.uchicago.edu/">The <i>Speculum
      Romanae Magnificentiae </i>Digital Collection</a><i></i><br
      /><blockquote><img
      alt="http://speculum.lib.uchicago.edu/images/speculum-banner.jpg" class="decoded" height="81"
      src="http://speculum.lib.uchicago.edu/images/speculum-banner.jpg" width="400"
      /></blockquote><br /><blockquote><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">The <i>Speculum Romanae Magnificentiae</i> is a collection of
      engravings of Rome and Roman antiquities, the core of which consists of prints published by
      Antonio Lafreri and gathered under a title page he printed in the mid-1570's. Copies of the
      <i>Speculum</i> vary greatly in the number of prints, and individual prints were
      reissued and changed over time. </span><br /><br style="height: 1em;"
      /><span style="font-size: x-small;">The University of Chicago Library's copy of the
      <i>Speculum Romanae Magnificentiae</i> contains nearly 1,000 prints and is the
      largest in the world. The Library's copy arrived in the 1890's as a part of the Berlin
      Collection, a large lot of books and manuscripts purchased for the Library from S. Calvary and
      Co. in Berlin.</span></blockquote><blockquote><div
      class="marqueerow"><div class="marquee"><span style="font-size:
      xx-small;"><img alt="" src="http://speculum.lib.uchicago.edu/images/marquee-intro.jpg"
      /></span> <br /><h2><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><a
